timeline_data.body:
> doubt asserts work during ASGCT (trace in general is disabled) ...

That might explain why I didn't see the application stop to dump the core even when it detected the signature's format is incorrect in `getSendSlotsFromSignature`. I also added the following code right after `Assert_Util_true(signature[0] == '(');` hoping to get a crash right there. 

```c
   Assert_Util_true(signature[0] == '(');

   if (signature[0] != '(') {
      *(volatile int*)(0) = 1;
      raise(SIGABRT);
      raise(SIGTRAP);
   }
```
I also run the test with `-Xdump:system+java+snap:events=user+gpf,request=exclusive+prepwalk+preempt`. With the extra code and -Xdump option, I get [the assert](https://github.com/eclipse-openj9/openj9/issues/20577#issuecomment-2491377496) at `performDecompile`. I suspect the sequence of events might be that something is wrong first with the decompilation and then later the hang happens in `AsyncGetCallTrace`.

